  INSERT INTO artists (name, sort_name, is_collective, bio, source_url, bio_source, bio_festival)
  VALUES ('East End Dubs', 'east end dubs', false, 'Personifying the underground London house sound in every way, you need only listen to a handful of East End Dubs’ releases to understand the deep impact that the city has had on him and his music. Fusing subtle throwbacks to acid-tinged warehouse raves with the groove of UK Garage, his music captures a feeling that can be traced back through the decades as he presents it to a new generation packaged with tight, rolling basslines and the precision drums which have become his production calling card.

His carefully curated Eastenderz label and events brand has cemented his place as a respected tastemaker in London, providing a platform for supporting new homegrown talent, as well as mainstay underground heavyweights. With over a decade of releases, Eastenderz now sits amongst some of the scene’s most respected imprints and looks set to develop into an integral part of the electronic music scene for years to come.

Constantly innovative, in the last years he took the label’s uncompromising party ethos to cities like Berlin, Barcelona, and Paris, selling-out venues like fabric, Watergate, E1 and Input among others. He then naturally followed with a summer in Ibiza, where he took Eastenderz to the terrace of Amnesia, followed by a monthly residency at Cova Santa, while in between shows he would be playing regularly at Amnesia for Paradise, as well as DC10 and Pacha for Music On.

With the summer finally over, there is still no rest for East End Dubs as he delivers his newest venture of ‘ExtENDed’. A project aimed at reconnecting with the journey of DJing, through longer, uninterrupted sets without musical limitation. Giving both the audience and East End Dubs time to solidify their connection. This concept will be hitting all the usual European hot spots, while also hopping across the Atlantic to be homed by Space, Miami, and Stereo, Montreal.', 'https://www.awakenings.com/en/artists/east-end-dubs/380096/', 'festival:awakenings-festival-2026', 'Personifying the underground London house sound in every way, you need only listen to a handful of East End Dubs’ releases to understand the deep impact that the city has had on him and his music. Fusing subtle throwbacks to acid-tinged warehouse raves with the groove of UK Garage, his music captures a feeling that can be traced back through the decades as he presents it to a new generation packaged with tight, rolling basslines and the precision drums which have become his production calling card.

His carefully curated Eastenderz label and events brand has cemented his place as a respected tastemaker in London, providing a platform for supporting new homegrown talent, as well as mainstay underground heavyweights. With over a decade of releases, Eastenderz now sits amongst some of the scene’s most respected imprints and looks set to develop into an integral part of the electronic music scene for years to come.

Constantly innovative, in the last years he took the label’s uncompromising party ethos to cities like Berlin, Barcelona, and Paris, selling-out venues like fabric, Watergate, E1 and Input among others. He then naturally followed with a summer in Ibiza, where he took Eastenderz to the terrace of Amnesia, followed by a monthly residency at Cova Santa, while in between shows he would be playing regularly at Amnesia for Paradise, as well as DC10 and Pacha for Music On.

With the summer finally over, there is still no rest for East End Dubs as he delivers his newest venture of ‘ExtENDed’. A project aimed at reconnecting with the journey of DJing, through longer, uninterrupted sets without musical limitation. Giving both the audience and East End Dubs time to solidify their connection. This concept will be hitting all the usual European hot spots, while also hopping across the Atlantic to be homed by Space, Miami, and Stereo, Montreal.')
