  INSERT INTO artists (name, sort_name, is_collective, bio, source_url, bio_source, bio_festival)
  VALUES ('Alan Fitzpatrick', 'alan fitzpatrick', false, 'Alan Fitzpatrick is the pre-eminent and most inuential UK based Techno artist. With a trailblazing career under his belt, a back catalogue of some of the most important Techno releases of a generation and events brand We Are The Brave, it’s clear that he is a leader within the global Techno scene.

Fitzpatrick has carved out his own musical niche holding rank in the upper echelons of the underground electronic world. Few artists can claim to have headlined Berghain, and also had a hit on daytime BBC Radio 1, but then there aren’t many artists like Alan Fitzpatrick. Consistently rubbing shoulders with the most inuential tastemakers of the Techno scene for over a decade, from Carl Cox and Adam Beyer to Nina Kraviz and Reinier Zonneveld, Fitzpatricks’s presence at the top table on the genre is undeniable. 

Known primarily for his raw hard- edged sound, Alan has developed into one of dance music’s most versatile producers, equally at home putting out techno bangers on Drumcode as he is making disco-infused house anthems, or experimental electronica under his 3STRANGE alias, not to mention his impressive range of collaborations.

His label We Are The Brave is a go-to label for anyone wishing to nd only the nest and most forward-thinking Techno. It’s that same forward-thinking mentality that inuences his groundbreaking WATB label events having already showcased his roster’s talent at The Warehouse Project Manchester, Shine Belfast, Watergate Berlin, SWG3 Glasgow and the infamous Fabric nightclub in London.

Fast-forward to today and this titan of UK Techno shows no sign of slowing down. Recent collaborations with the likes of Lilly Palmer, Joyhauser, and Hi-Lo plus a slew of releases scheduled for coming months surely further demonstrate Fitzpatrick’s star continues to rise.', 'https://www.awakenings.com/en/artists/alan-fitzpatrick/36/', 'festival:awakenings-festival-2026', 'Alan Fitzpatrick is the pre-eminent and most inuential UK based Techno artist. With a trailblazing career under his belt, a back catalogue of some of the most important Techno releases of a generation and events brand We Are The Brave, it’s clear that he is a leader within the global Techno scene.

Fitzpatrick has carved out his own musical niche holding rank in the upper echelons of the underground electronic world. Few artists can claim to have headlined Berghain, and also had a hit on daytime BBC Radio 1, but then there aren’t many artists like Alan Fitzpatrick. Consistently rubbing shoulders with the most inuential tastemakers of the Techno scene for over a decade, from Carl Cox and Adam Beyer to Nina Kraviz and Reinier Zonneveld, Fitzpatricks’s presence at the top table on the genre is undeniable. 

Known primarily for his raw hard- edged sound, Alan has developed into one of dance music’s most versatile producers, equally at home putting out techno bangers on Drumcode as he is making disco-infused house anthems, or experimental electronica under his 3STRANGE alias, not to mention his impressive range of collaborations.

His label We Are The Brave is a go-to label for anyone wishing to nd only the nest and most forward-thinking Techno. It’s that same forward-thinking mentality that inuences his groundbreaking WATB label events having already showcased his roster’s talent at The Warehouse Project Manchester, Shine Belfast, Watergate Berlin, SWG3 Glasgow and the infamous Fabric nightclub in London.

Fast-forward to today and this titan of UK Techno shows no sign of slowing down. Recent collaborations with the likes of Lilly Palmer, Joyhauser, and Hi-Lo plus a slew of releases scheduled for coming months surely further demonstrate Fitzpatrick’s star continues to rise.')
