  INSERT INTO artists (name, sort_name, is_collective, bio, source_url, bio_source, bio_festival)
  VALUES ('Franc Fala', 'franc fala', false, 'Over the past few years, he has developed a distinct signature, unorthodox, emotionally charged, and rhythmic, that has been resonating within the city’s underground club community. Franc’s journey has seen him performing at some of Amsterdam’s most iconic venues, including Shelter, Het Sieraad, and De Marktkantine, Now, Franc’s sights are set on breaking borders and making an impact on the international stage. And 2025 is already shaping up to be proof of that ambition. With a touring schedule that spans cities across Europe, as well as performances in Dubai, Turkey, Mexico, Canada, Georgia, Kazakhstan, and Azerbaijan, Franc Fala is steadily carving out his space globally. Landmark appearances at venues and festivals like Pacha Ibiza, Ushuaïa, Chinois, Tomorrowland, Loveland, Mysteryland, No Art Festival, Keinemusik Amsterdam, Sziget, and Untold highlight a year that marks a meaningful step into the international house scene. And all of this within the first year of his breakthrough.

With the success of his hit, ''Yamore,'' Franc Fala has solidified his position as the one to keep your eye on within the international house scene. The track, a collaboration with MoBlack, Salif Keita, Benja, and Cesária Evora, has surpassed 190 million streams on Spotify, capturing the essence of Franc''s ability to merge diverse influences into a cohesive, club-ready anthem. The production process, which spanned over a year and a half, exemplifies Franc’s meticulous approach and commitment to perfection. The track’s powerful second half, with its big stage energy, took center stage when played at the Brooklyn Mirage, a moment that Franc describes as both surreal and defining. His follow-up collaboration with Amémé, Wait for You, further solidified his status as a distinctive and forward-thinking producer, earning over 3.5 million streams and strong international support. Releases that followed, like 5AM Jungle Jam and La Luz, the latter once again alongside Benja, showcased his deep connection to the underground house scene. La Luz made its mark even before its official release, with early support from industry heavyweights such as Adriatique, Mau P, Gordo, Mahmut Orhan, Cincity, Francis Mercier, and others, establishing Franc Fala as an artist whose work resonates across a wide spectrum of the scene’s leading figures.

Driven by the element of surprise and a refusal to be boxed into one genre, Franc Fala’s sound is a dynamic blend of house and beyond. He believes in transcending musical boundaries and creating something unexpected, which keeps his audience engaged and on their toes. This artistic philosophy is summed up in his own words: “To transcend the daily. To enlighten the things worth remembering.” Franc’s upcoming projects include new releases on high profile labels where he continues to refine a style that’s both house and groove-focused yet constantly innovative.

As he continues to build on the momentum of ''Yamore,'' Franc is poised to make waves worldwide. Keep an eye out for Franc Fala as he takes his signature sound and stage presence to the next level, one track and one stage at a time.', 'https://www.awakenings.com/en/artists/franc-fala/386603/', 'festival:awakenings-festival-2026', 'Over the past few years, he has developed a distinct signature, unorthodox, emotionally charged, and rhythmic, that has been resonating within the city’s underground club community. Franc’s journey has seen him performing at some of Amsterdam’s most iconic venues, including Shelter, Het Sieraad, and De Marktkantine, Now, Franc’s sights are set on breaking borders and making an impact on the international stage. And 2025 is already shaping up to be proof of that ambition. With a touring schedule that spans cities across Europe, as well as performances in Dubai, Turkey, Mexico, Canada, Georgia, Kazakhstan, and Azerbaijan, Franc Fala is steadily carving out his space globally. Landmark appearances at venues and festivals like Pacha Ibiza, Ushuaïa, Chinois, Tomorrowland, Loveland, Mysteryland, No Art Festival, Keinemusik Amsterdam, Sziget, and Untold highlight a year that marks a meaningful step into the international house scene. And all of this within the first year of his breakthrough.

With the success of his hit, ''Yamore,'' Franc Fala has solidified his position as the one to keep your eye on within the international house scene. The track, a collaboration with MoBlack, Salif Keita, Benja, and Cesária Evora, has surpassed 190 million streams on Spotify, capturing the essence of Franc''s ability to merge diverse influences into a cohesive, club-ready anthem. The production process, which spanned over a year and a half, exemplifies Franc’s meticulous approach and commitment to perfection. The track’s powerful second half, with its big stage energy, took center stage when played at the Brooklyn Mirage, a moment that Franc describes as both surreal and defining. His follow-up collaboration with Amémé, Wait for You, further solidified his status as a distinctive and forward-thinking producer, earning over 3.5 million streams and strong international support. Releases that followed, like 5AM Jungle Jam and La Luz, the latter once again alongside Benja, showcased his deep connection to the underground house scene. La Luz made its mark even before its official release, with early support from industry heavyweights such as Adriatique, Mau P, Gordo, Mahmut Orhan, Cincity, Francis Mercier, and others, establishing Franc Fala as an artist whose work resonates across a wide spectrum of the scene’s leading figures.

Driven by the element of surprise and a refusal to be boxed into one genre, Franc Fala’s sound is a dynamic blend of house and beyond. He believes in transcending musical boundaries and creating something unexpected, which keeps his audience engaged and on their toes. This artistic philosophy is summed up in his own words: “To transcend the daily. To enlighten the things worth remembering.” Franc’s upcoming projects include new releases on high profile labels where he continues to refine a style that’s both house and groove-focused yet constantly innovative.

As he continues to build on the momentum of ''Yamore,'' Franc is poised to make waves worldwide. Keep an eye out for Franc Fala as he takes his signature sound and stage presence to the next level, one track and one stage at a time.')
