  INSERT INTO artists (name, sort_name, is_collective, bio, source_url, bio_source, bio_festival)
  VALUES ('Adam Ten', 'adam ten', false, 'Adam has shaped and developed his own unique sound and has become one of leading names in the underground scene within the Mediterranean ‘City of Lights’.

Adam spent years playing regularly at key clubs in Tel Aviv and was a resident at the legendary venue ‘The Block’. He is no stranger to playing all night long - his versatility and curiosity as a DJ means he floats with the crowd, taking them on a smooth journey, fluently mixing a wide range of genres.

In the last few years Adam has played iconic sets at major events such as Burning Man, Coachella, Circoloco, Mayan Warrior, Lightning in a Bottle, and EDC Vegas, as well as legendary venues including London’s Fabric & Printworks, Pacha & DC10 in Ibiza and Space Miami, whilst conquering South America and everywhere else in between.

His Maccabi House label, founded with good friend Mita Gami, stands for music that pushes the boundaries of regular house, adding a psychedelic and funky twist. Promoting and releasing top records from rising talent in Tel-Aviv, the label has grown rapidly in the last two years, reaching 1st place on Beatport within its genre, and putting on sell-out branded events in major markets such as LA, NYC and Tulum. Adam is also the co-founder of ‘TERRA’, which puts on some of the biggest open-air events in his home country.

As a producer, Adam’s tracks have gained worldwide recognition with releases on Diynamic, Crosstown Rebels, Higher Ground, Disco Halal and his own Maccabi House imprint. In the last 3 years, more than 20 of his tracks were in Beatport ‘Top 10’ lists. His big summer release of 2023, ‘Spring Girl’, hit 1st place overall on Beatport and his recent collaboration with artist Rhye, ‘3 Days Later’, amassed over a million streams in 2 weeks!

Adam’s music is regularly supported by a wide selection of artists such as Solomun, Michael Bibi, Damian Lazarus, Dixon, Tale Of Us, DJ Tennis, Black Coffee, WhoMadeWho, Rufus Du Sol and Adriatique, to name a few... Diplo recently described him as ''the best producer in the game right now’.', 'https://www.awakenings.com/en/artists/adam-ten/386480/', 'festival:awakenings-festival-2026', 'Adam has shaped and developed his own unique sound and has become one of leading names in the underground scene within the Mediterranean ‘City of Lights’.

Adam spent years playing regularly at key clubs in Tel Aviv and was a resident at the legendary venue ‘The Block’. He is no stranger to playing all night long - his versatility and curiosity as a DJ means he floats with the crowd, taking them on a smooth journey, fluently mixing a wide range of genres.

In the last few years Adam has played iconic sets at major events such as Burning Man, Coachella, Circoloco, Mayan Warrior, Lightning in a Bottle, and EDC Vegas, as well as legendary venues including London’s Fabric & Printworks, Pacha & DC10 in Ibiza and Space Miami, whilst conquering South America and everywhere else in between.

His Maccabi House label, founded with good friend Mita Gami, stands for music that pushes the boundaries of regular house, adding a psychedelic and funky twist. Promoting and releasing top records from rising talent in Tel-Aviv, the label has grown rapidly in the last two years, reaching 1st place on Beatport within its genre, and putting on sell-out branded events in major markets such as LA, NYC and Tulum. Adam is also the co-founder of ‘TERRA’, which puts on some of the biggest open-air events in his home country.

As a producer, Adam’s tracks have gained worldwide recognition with releases on Diynamic, Crosstown Rebels, Higher Ground, Disco Halal and his own Maccabi House imprint. In the last 3 years, more than 20 of his tracks were in Beatport ‘Top 10’ lists. His big summer release of 2023, ‘Spring Girl’, hit 1st place overall on Beatport and his recent collaboration with artist Rhye, ‘3 Days Later’, amassed over a million streams in 2 weeks!

Adam’s music is regularly supported by a wide selection of artists such as Solomun, Michael Bibi, Damian Lazarus, Dixon, Tale Of Us, DJ Tennis, Black Coffee, WhoMadeWho, Rufus Du Sol and Adriatique, to name a few... Diplo recently described him as ''the best producer in the game right now’.')
