  INSERT INTO artists (name, sort_name, is_collective, bio, source_url, bio_source, bio_festival)
  VALUES ('Julian Fijma', 'julian fijma', false, 'Hailing from the quaint city of Enkhuizen in the Netherlands, 24-year-old Julian Fijma is a rising star in the underground electronic music scene. Currently based in Hoorn, near Amsterdam, Julian has been making waves with his distinctive sound and array of releases on some of the most established labels in the genre, which gained support of well-known DJ''s like East End Dubs, Chris Stussy, Josh Baker and Enzo Siragusa.

Julian takes inspiration from many different music genres and styles with which he crafts his own unique sound consisting of heavy basslines, refreshing synths and groovy drums. A typical track of his has a distinctive recognisable modern sound that aims to evoke emotions in its listeners. With the success of his Airtime EP "The Way'' he gained the attention of some of the most respected artists in the scene. Followed by this success he managed to prove his ability once again and scored himself his first no.1 release in the Beatport Minimal/Deep Tech Charts with his ''Sweet Resonance EP'' on the UK based label WYLD.

Julian’s journey in music took a pivotal turn through his connection with East End Dubs’ very own Eastenderz. Over the past few years, Eastenderz has played a significant role in mentoring Julian, offering him invaluable guidance and support, leading to the release of his “ENDZ055“ EP in 2023. Julian recently made this return to the Eastenderz imprint with his “Bad City” EP, the most successful and highly streamed release of his to date.

2025 is set to be a year of continued growth for Julian. With his coming releases already gaining
wide support and big anticipation from his audience. With his unique sound, meticulous production style, and growing recognition in the electronic music scene, Julian Fijma is set to leave an indelible mark as he continues to captivate audiences worldwide. Watch out for him in a city near you.', 'https://www.awakenings.com/en/artists/julian-fijma/386468/', 'festival:awakenings-festival-2026', 'Hailing from the quaint city of Enkhuizen in the Netherlands, 24-year-old Julian Fijma is a rising star in the underground electronic music scene. Currently based in Hoorn, near Amsterdam, Julian has been making waves with his distinctive sound and array of releases on some of the most established labels in the genre, which gained support of well-known DJ''s like East End Dubs, Chris Stussy, Josh Baker and Enzo Siragusa.

Julian takes inspiration from many different music genres and styles with which he crafts his own unique sound consisting of heavy basslines, refreshing synths and groovy drums. A typical track of his has a distinctive recognisable modern sound that aims to evoke emotions in its listeners. With the success of his Airtime EP "The Way'' he gained the attention of some of the most respected artists in the scene. Followed by this success he managed to prove his ability once again and scored himself his first no.1 release in the Beatport Minimal/Deep Tech Charts with his ''Sweet Resonance EP'' on the UK based label WYLD.

Julian’s journey in music took a pivotal turn through his connection with East End Dubs’ very own Eastenderz. Over the past few years, Eastenderz has played a significant role in mentoring Julian, offering him invaluable guidance and support, leading to the release of his “ENDZ055“ EP in 2023. Julian recently made this return to the Eastenderz imprint with his “Bad City” EP, the most successful and highly streamed release of his to date.

2025 is set to be a year of continued growth for Julian. With his coming releases already gaining
wide support and big anticipation from his audience. With his unique sound, meticulous production style, and growing recognition in the electronic music scene, Julian Fijma is set to leave an indelible mark as he continues to captivate audiences worldwide. Watch out for him in a city near you.')
