  INSERT INTO artists (name, sort_name, is_collective, bio, source_url, bio_source, bio_festival)
  VALUES ('Shwelly M', 'shwelly m', false, 'Shwelly M is one of Cape Town’s most exciting new Afrotech voices — a South African DJ, producer, and
vocalist turning 26 this year, whose high-energy sets are reshaping contemporary African dancefloors.
A graduate of the Bridges Academy (Class of 2022), she represents a new generation of artists merging
cultural depth with forward-thinking club music.

Her sound moves fluidly between Afrotech, 3-Step, and Gqom, driven by hypnotic percussion, driving
low-end, and moments of vocal release that elevate both club rooms and festival stages. Known for her
powerful stage presence, Shwelly M delivers performances that balance intensity, groove, and
emotional connection — earning her a reputation as a crowd-shaping selector with a clear artistic
identity.

In 2023, she reached a major career milestone by headlining Black Coffee One Man Show, cementing
her position as a trusted and battle-tested performer. Since then, she has continued to build momentum
through consistent appearances across South Africa and features on multiple releases, establishing
herself as both a DJ and creator to watch.

Beyond performance, Shwelly M has emerged as a respected tastemaker within the global electronic
ecosystem. Recently featured on Inflyte during Women’s Month, she represented South African DJs
actively connecting with producers and selectors worldwide. As part of the Umgido Records Inflyte
promo pool, she contributes feedback on unreleased music alongside international tastemakers,
shaping final versions and reflecting this global exchange directly in her forward-thinking sets.

As she notes:
“On Inflyte with Umgido Records, you’re not just hearing music, you’re shaping it. Your feedback
reaches artists, and every voice, download, and connection moves us closer to raising that 17.6%”

Alongside her growing influence online, including a highly engaged and fast-growing TikTok presence,
Shwelly M continues to expand the reach of South African electronic music beyond its borders.
2026 marks a defining international chapter, with an upcoming European tour featuring appearances at
Garbicz Festival, Kater Blau, and The Other Side, among others. In parallel, she is set to release a string
of new music throughout the year on BFM Records, highlighting both her production evolution and vocal
versatility.

With a bold vision, growing global relevance, and a sound rooted in South African innovation, Shwelly M
is no longer emerging, she is arriving.', 'https://www.awakenings.com/en/artists/shwelly-m/396297/', 'festival:awakenings-festival-2026', 'Shwelly M is one of Cape Town’s most exciting new Afrotech voices — a South African DJ, producer, and
vocalist turning 26 this year, whose high-energy sets are reshaping contemporary African dancefloors.
A graduate of the Bridges Academy (Class of 2022), she represents a new generation of artists merging
cultural depth with forward-thinking club music.

Her sound moves fluidly between Afrotech, 3-Step, and Gqom, driven by hypnotic percussion, driving
low-end, and moments of vocal release that elevate both club rooms and festival stages. Known for her
powerful stage presence, Shwelly M delivers performances that balance intensity, groove, and
emotional connection — earning her a reputation as a crowd-shaping selector with a clear artistic
identity.

In 2023, she reached a major career milestone by headlining Black Coffee One Man Show, cementing
her position as a trusted and battle-tested performer. Since then, she has continued to build momentum
through consistent appearances across South Africa and features on multiple releases, establishing
herself as both a DJ and creator to watch.

Beyond performance, Shwelly M has emerged as a respected tastemaker within the global electronic
ecosystem. Recently featured on Inflyte during Women’s Month, she represented South African DJs
actively connecting with producers and selectors worldwide. As part of the Umgido Records Inflyte
promo pool, she contributes feedback on unreleased music alongside international tastemakers,
shaping final versions and reflecting this global exchange directly in her forward-thinking sets.

As she notes:
“On Inflyte with Umgido Records, you’re not just hearing music, you’re shaping it. Your feedback
reaches artists, and every voice, download, and connection moves us closer to raising that 17.6%”

Alongside her growing influence online, including a highly engaged and fast-growing TikTok presence,
Shwelly M continues to expand the reach of South African electronic music beyond its borders.
2026 marks a defining international chapter, with an upcoming European tour featuring appearances at
Garbicz Festival, Kater Blau, and The Other Side, among others. In parallel, she is set to release a string
of new music throughout the year on BFM Records, highlighting both her production evolution and vocal
versatility.

With a bold vision, growing global relevance, and a sound rooted in South African innovation, Shwelly M
is no longer emerging, she is arriving.')
